President Obama called Tony Stewart to congratulate him and the Stewart-Haas Racing team on winning the 2011 Sprint Cup Series Championship. The President was impressed with Stewart's ability to come from the back of the pack to win the championship. He also mentioned that the First Lady and Dr. Biden enjoyed attending the Ford 400 race at Homestead and appreciated NASCAR's support for military families. The President praised Stewart and the other drivers for being positive role models and ambassadors for NASCAR. He expressed his desire to personally congratulate Stewart at the White House next year.